# MandoMC — config and resources

## Defaults

- Ship defaults under `src/main/resources/` so `saveResource` / first-run copy works. Nested paths must match what `BaseConfig` (or loaders) expect under the plugin data folder.
- Prefer additive config changes with safe defaults to avoid breaking existing live server files after update.

## Typed configs

- Prefer subclasses of `net.mandomc.core.config.BaseConfig` for typed getters, `reload()`, and consistent missing-key warnings.
- Keep parsing/validation close to the config class and return sane fallback values on invalid entries.

## Reload

- Full plugin reload is `MandoMC.reload()` (e.g. `/mmcreload`): modules disable/re-enable; `ConfigModule` runs again and reconstructs typed configs registered in `ServiceRegistry`.
- If you add a new config service, register it in `ConfigModule` in the correct **dependency order** (see comments there for items, vehicles, shops). Ensure any long-lived tasks or listeners read fresh config after reload if needed.
- Document any config that cannot be hot-reloaded and require restart only if absolutely unavoidable.
